**Problem:** Manual try/catch is verbose and fragile. If someone removes the `Assert.Fail`, the test silently passes when no exception is thrown. MSTest has a built-in mechanism.

**Fix:** Use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>`:

```csharp
var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ValidationException>(
    () => processor.ProcessOrder(order));

Assert.AreEqual("Order must contain at least one item", ex.Message);
```

